# Go to root folder
cd ~/distributed-systems-homelab

# Create .gitignore
cat > .gitignore << 'EOF'

# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Environment Variables
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# NEVER commit real .env files
# They contain passwords and secrets
.env
.env.local
.env.development
.env.production
.env.test

# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Node.js Dependencies
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Never push node_modules
# Run npm install to recreate
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Mac System Files
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Thumbs.db

# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Logs
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
logs/
*.log

# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Editor Files
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

EOF
```

---

## What Each Section Does

### Section 1 — Environment Variables
```
.env               ← your actual passwords
.env.local         ← local overrides
.env.development   ← dev environment
.env.production    ← production secrets
.env.test          ← test environment

All ignored ✅
Only .env.example
goes to GitHub ✅
```

---

### Section 2 — Node Modules
```
node_modules/  ← all day folders covered
               day1-zomato/node_modules ❌
               day2-upi/node_modules    ❌
               day3-whatsapp/node_modules❌

npm-debug.log  ← npm error logs
yarn-debug.log ← yarn error logs
```

---

### Section 3 — Mac System Files
```
.DS_Store   ← Mac folder settings
             (created automatically
              by Mac Finder)
             Very annoying on GitHub
             Always ignore this ✅
```

---

### Section 4 — Logs
```
logs/   ← any log folders
*.log   ← any log files

Your simulations may
generate log files
All ignored ✅
```

---

### Section 5 — Editor Files
```
.vscode/  ← VS Code settings
.idea/    ← IntelliJ settings
*.swp     ← Vim swap files
*.swo     ← Vim swap files

These are personal
editor preferences
Nobody else needs them ✅